spanGrp.span: In the old times, Kinting-kintang-pa's story
He said: "My cultivation time has come now"
He said: "Let me go to cultivate the fields"
and while he was sharpening his sword
A crab came and bit his testicles
vakāng dato vājungsin nāte ṭhu̠m hru̠ vāveval
and since he was frightened, he cut down a fruit thread
ṭhu̠m hru̠ ijung butuwng tarih to vadeengval
The fruit that he cut down fell over and hit a jungle fowl
timpahrang to vājung chun nāte pangal pa adal vapa keval
Then the Ant came out and bit Boar's testicles
Ran down and entered inside an elephant ear.
pase na- tuwng aro dọnu̠ vajung chun nā
the elephant shouted "Heyǃǃǃ" and ran down
and stamped over a widow's hut
now the widow appealed (to the King)
pase kāthal penu̠ dọnu̠ vavakāh nāte
was destroyed by an elephant, as she claimed
pase nangte hmikhu̠nu̠ in athal rumvā
"Why did you destroy the widow's hut?"
kapo thamnu̠ the moongkol diinu̠ kachachā memeh te
"since I was hungry, I was just eating bananas and"
this Bat entered inside my ear
amatuwng kachun nā hmikhu̠nu̠ in kathal va
that's why while running I have destroyed the widow's hut
The King: Bat, why do you enter inside others' ears?
miing dadah kāpake naka kācha naka dọọnu̠
of someone who could eat me, I was hiding myself
I was just staying properly inside the banana plants.
a Boar came and punched me out
The King: You Boar, why did you punch out the bat?
nite athe kaamcha jāte chincha kachachā memeh te
While I was just behaving properly and eating the food
This Ant came and bit my testicles
The King: You Timpahrang (Ant), why did you bite others testicles?
hnabu̠h thung ataheeng kāhre jānāte. Tarih...
"But while I was just hiding properly in my ant-nest
tarihpa kāthe hlonu̠ tuki kachun nā kapake vaveh
this Jungle fowl came and scratched me out, so I ran and bit (the boar)
tarih, nang dahki maram timpahrang te āthe lolvāh
The King: Jungle fowl, why did you scratch out the ant?
while I was just staying like that
ṭhu̠m nang dahki miing adeeng vāh
The King: You fruit, why do you hit others?
while I was just hanging on myself properly
As I fell down, I hit the Rooster
The King: Tingkin-tingtang-pa, why do you cut others down?
nite kakum (kumli) vika, dọnu̠ kāng kāda chāte
As for me, since my cultivation time has come, I was sharpening my sword
A crab came and bit my testicles
The King: crab, why do you bite others testicles?
eāl to vathe nahrang am macha juwlcha
But the Crab had nothing to say, so he lost
hmikhu̠nu̠ in licho nahrangki sọọl bāl junglih
Go and bring the money to compensate for the widow's hut
lidar to ahang sin lom lomnu̠
He came back rolling a renowing tray uphill
This is just a renowing tray, what's the use of it?
he came back rolling uphill a mortar
The King: what is this mortar good for?
now the crab went and just stayed sitting at home
since, he just stayed at home
(The king): "Go and see why he is not coming."
They went and he is sitting at home
He is just sitting at home
And when they smashed him with a pestle
pheh rum nu̠ amatuwng esọ atungheeng
He got flattened. the crab. so that's why now
